FileHandling:
-- filehandling in java means reading and writing the data to the files

    steps:
        1. find the path of the file
        2. create the objects of FileInputStream/FileOutputStream
        3. Depending upon the file type we create the object of properties/ XSSFWorkbook
        4. We read the data/write the data and close our file
=================================================================================================
exceptions are some kind of issues/errors that disrupts the normal flow of code during runtime and
other important lines of code are not executed due to that issue